"v.抱怨 【英】 v.抱怨(to complain naggingly) 【考】 gripe : discontent / praise : admiration(因为不满而抱怨/因 为赞赏而赞扬) v. 抱怨; 发牢骚 = grumble; 抓紧, 抓住 = grasp = seize 【记】gripe = grow ripe变得成熟－又老了一岁, 很多人会抱怨. Gripe源于grasp(n /v 抓住; 掌握), 所以gripping(adj 引起人注意的) 【类】gripe: discontent = praise: admiration抱怨表达不满 = 赞扬表达赞赏 【记】源自grasp；抓人的，挠人心的，令人烦燥的，现在人们都紧抓着手里的东西不放，还发牢骚抱怨没抓到的东西；音：给，割 + ripe 熟，去吃烤肉，给割点熟的(肉)，别老给半生不熟的 gripe (v.)  Old English gripan ""grasp at, lay hold, attack, take, seek to get hold of,"" from Proto-Germanic *gripan (cognates: Old Saxon gripan, Old Norse gripa, Dutch grijpen, Gothic greipan, Old High German grifan, German greifen ""to seize""), from PIE root *ghreib- ""to grip"" (cognates: Lithuanian griebiu ""to seize""). Figurative sense of ""complain, grouse"" is first attested 1932, probably from earlier meaning ""gripping pain in the bowels"" (c.1600; compare bellyache). Related: Griped; griping. gripe (n.)  late 14c., from gripe (v.). Figurative sense by 1934."
